l acetate?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Directly inhibits follicle stimulating hormone release","Selective oestrogen receptor modulation","Prevents implantation through endometrial disruption","Selective progesterone receptor modulation","Causes immediate breakdown of corpus luteum"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EUlipristal acetate works through \u003Cstrong\u003Eselective progesterone receptor modulation\u003C/strong\u003E. It binds to progesterone receptors and prevents or delays ovulation by suppressing the luteinising hormone surge. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe other answers are incorrect as explained below:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDirectly inhibiting follicle stimulating hormone release\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect as ulipristal does not directly affect FSH release from the anterior pituitary.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESelective oestrogen receptor modulation\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect as ulipristal is selective for progesterone receptors and does not have significant activity at oestrogen receptors.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPreventing implantation through endometrial disruption\u003C/strong\u003E is an effect of mifepristone. \u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECausing immediate breakdown of corpus luteum\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect as ulipristal does not cause immediate luteolysis; its main action is on preventing or delaying ovulation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUlipristal is effective for emergency contraception up to 120 hours after unprotected intercourse, which is longer than levonorgestrel-based emergency contraception.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Ulipristal acetate is a selective progesterone receptor modulator.","Ulipristal is effec